  "original_title": "Sri Lanka has enough fuel to distribute : CPC",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka has enough fuel to distribute : CPC",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s state-run Ceylon Petroleum Corporation has said it has enough diesel, petrol and kerosene both imported and refined locally and assures the public there will be no shortage, as few fuel queues started forming for the first time since a QR-code fuel ration system was introduced.",
        "\u201cCPC has diesel, petrol and kerosene available to distribute without a shortage. The refinery has started operations and steps have been taken to produce all fuel.,\u201d a statement said.",
        "\u201cImported fuel is also available in the Kolonnawa and Murthurajawela storage facilities.\u201d",
        "CPC Is in the process of distributing the fuel and advised the public not to get distressed unnecessarily."
      ],
